WEBVTT

00:00:12.221 --> 00:00:17.351
[phone rings]

00:00:18.268 --> 00:00:19.394
Hello?

00:00:19.436 --> 00:00:21.438
[RENA giggles]
Good morning, Keiichi!

00:00:21.480 --> 00:00:22.898
Wake up, sleepyhead!

00:00:22.940 --> 00:00:23.982
Wake up!

00:00:24.024 --> 00:00:24.983
[KEIICHI]
Rena?

00:00:25.025 --> 00:00:26.652
Why are you calling me so early?

00:00:26.693 --> 00:00:28.904
[MION]
Good morning, Kei!

00:00:28.946 --> 00:00:30.572
You too, Mion?

00:00:30.614 --> 00:00:32.032
Another challenge?

00:00:32.074 --> 00:00:33.492
[MION]
Glad you're finally figuring out

00:00:33.534 --> 00:00:35.369
how this club works, bud.

00:00:35.410 --> 00:00:38.539
We're gonna meet at the
usual spot before we head out.

00:00:38.580 --> 00:00:40.707
We'll be seeing you
there, right?

00:00:40.749 --> 00:00:41.917
You bet you will!

00:00:41.959 --> 00:00:44.086
And I'll hand you
your butt on a platter!

00:00:44.670 --> 00:00:45.629
[RENA]
Keiichi!

00:00:45.671 --> 00:00:47.548
What took you so long?

00:00:48.632 --> 00:00:50.634
Sorry about that, guys!

00:01:01.937 --> 00:01:03.647
[SATOKO]
You're finally here!

00:01:03.689 --> 00:01:05.732
We've been waiting patiently!

00:01:05.774 --> 00:01:06.525
Good morning.

00:01:06.567 --> 00:01:07.943
Glad to see you made it.

00:01:07.985 --> 00:01:08.694
You too!

00:01:08.735 --> 00:01:10.404
What's on the agenda today?

00:01:11.071 --> 00:01:11.738
[KEIICHI]
Hold on.

00:01:11.780 --> 00:01:13.740
You mean this is where
we'll be having club?

00:01:13.782 --> 00:01:15.409
Yeah, the shop sets up
tournaments now

00:01:15.450 --> 00:01:18.912
and then to show off the
products and get new customers.

00:01:18.954 --> 00:01:21.415
A tournament. So now you're
telling me I'm gonna be playing

00:01:21.456 --> 00:01:23.667
against everybody else
in the whole shop?

00:01:23.709 --> 00:01:24.918
Exactly.

00:01:24.960 --> 00:01:26.878
Today's club meeting is special,
'cause there's more

00:01:26.920 --> 00:01:29.840
than just the five of us
competing this time around!

00:01:29.881 --> 00:01:31.675
Special, huh?

00:01:31.717 --> 00:01:34.094
I've got a lot more
people to beat now.

00:01:34.136 --> 00:01:34.886
[MION]
Okay, guys.

00:01:34.928 --> 00:01:36.221
Listen up!

00:01:36.722 --> 00:01:38.724
We've got 15 players total.

00:01:38.765 --> 00:01:40.934
First, we draw numbers
out of a hat.

00:01:40.976 --> 00:01:42.394
We'll split into
five groups of three,

00:01:42.436 --> 00:01:44.896
and the winner of
each group will advance.

00:01:53.864 --> 00:01:55.032
Oh, wow, can you guys believe

00:01:55.073 --> 00:01:57.784
we managed to end up in
separate groups somehow?

00:01:57.826 --> 00:01:59.077
Crazy.

00:01:59.119 --> 00:02:01.246
Honestly. You didn't
think I was gonna let

00:02:01.288 --> 00:02:04.082
any of us get bumped off
in round one, right?

00:02:04.124 --> 00:02:06.335
Heh. I have no idea
how you pulled that off,

00:02:06.376 --> 00:02:08.795
but either way,
I'm ready to smoke someone!

00:02:08.837 --> 00:02:11.006
All right, let's do it, Keiichi!

00:02:11.548 --> 00:02:12.382
Okay, then.

00:02:12.424 --> 00:02:14.343
I'll see you all in the finals!

00:02:14.384 --> 00:02:16.762
I'll be doing
my best to win, too!

00:02:21.558 --> 00:02:22.392
Oh hey.

00:02:22.434 --> 00:02:24.478
We're in class together,
aren't we?

00:02:24.519 --> 00:02:25.604
Yeah, that's right.

00:02:25.646 --> 00:02:27.147
I'm Tomita.

00:02:27.189 --> 00:02:28.815
Okamura.

00:02:28.857 --> 00:02:30.692
[KEIICHI] I can walk
right over these kids.

00:02:30.734 --> 00:02:32.527
They're not even
gonna see it coming!

00:02:32.569 --> 00:02:34.029
Good draw!

00:02:34.071 --> 00:02:34.946
Okay, guys.

00:02:34.988 --> 00:02:37.991
If everybody's set up,
let's get our games started!

00:02:38.033 --> 00:02:39.368
Here we go!

00:02:44.539 --> 00:02:46.375
One, two, three, four.

00:02:46.416 --> 00:02:49.586
Five thousand bucks each to
celebrate the birth of my child.

00:02:49.628 --> 00:02:51.254
Tough break, huh?

00:02:52.172 --> 00:02:54.883
Bonus time. Get a
hundred grand from the bank!

00:02:54.925 --> 00:02:55.467
Wha...?

00:02:55.509 --> 00:02:57.719
You already got
your money back already!

00:02:58.845 --> 00:03:00.555
I'm on the corporate ladder!

00:03:00.597 --> 00:03:03.308
[KEIICHI]
That's one of the best routes!

00:03:03.350 --> 00:03:06.186
This whole game
completely depends on luck!

00:03:06.228 --> 00:03:07.729
How am I supposed
to improve my chances

00:03:07.771 --> 00:03:10.482
when the game is just
spinning a roulette wheel?

00:03:10.524 --> 00:03:11.817
[GAMER A]
That's impossible!

00:03:11.858 --> 00:03:13.110
[GAMER B]
What are you, psychic?

00:03:13.151 --> 00:03:14.444
[SATOKO chortles]

00:03:14.486 --> 00:03:16.071
Good game, boys.

00:03:16.113 --> 00:03:19.491
But in the end, victory is mine!

00:03:19.533 --> 00:03:21.034
You've been outplayed.

00:03:21.076 --> 00:03:22.703
Wha... Seriously?

00:03:22.744 --> 00:03:24.538
You got through
your group already?

00:03:24.579 --> 00:03:26.123
Well done, Satoko.

00:03:26.164 --> 00:03:28.583
I see you've made
your way to the finals as well.

00:03:28.625 --> 00:03:31.503
No way, Mion too?
How'd that happen?

00:03:31.545 --> 00:03:32.713
So that's dealt with.

00:03:32.754 --> 00:03:35.215
What say we step out
for a cup of tea?

00:03:35.257 --> 00:03:37.759
The others should be
done by the time we get back.

00:03:37.801 --> 00:03:40.137
Ooh. Good idea!

00:03:43.223 --> 00:03:44.933
Are you for real?

00:03:44.975 --> 00:03:46.768
So how's it going for Rena?

00:03:46.810 --> 00:03:48.103
Okay, next card.

00:03:48.145 --> 00:03:50.063
"Every dog has its day."

00:03:52.524 --> 00:03:54.276
Awoo! It's so kyute!

00:03:54.317 --> 00:03:55.777
I wanna take it home!

00:03:55.819 --> 00:03:57.404
"A bird in hand is worth."

00:03:58.697 --> 00:04:00.949
[YOSHIRO]
"A fool and his money are‐‐"

00:04:00.991 --> 00:04:02.033
"Do unto others as‐‐"

00:04:02.075 --> 00:04:04.578
Awwo! I'm taking them home.

00:04:04.619 --> 00:04:06.079
They're so adorable!

00:04:06.121 --> 00:04:07.497
Awoo!

00:04:07.539 --> 00:04:08.373
[KEIICHI]
There's no way!

00:04:08.415 --> 00:04:10.125
She never plays
that hard at anything,

00:04:10.167 --> 00:04:11.835
so what's going on here?

00:04:11.877 --> 00:04:12.961
[gasps]

00:04:13.003 --> 00:04:13.754
Oh come on.

00:04:13.795 --> 00:04:16.339
The cards flipped
her cute switch?

00:04:17.382 --> 00:04:19.009
And Rika?

00:04:19.050 --> 00:04:20.093
[RIKA]
Mii!

00:04:20.135 --> 00:04:21.970
I got a fish, you guys!

00:04:22.012 --> 00:04:22.971
That's awesome.

00:04:23.013 --> 00:04:24.598
You're great at this, Rika!

00:04:24.639 --> 00:04:26.099
[RIKA]
Mii!

00:04:26.141 --> 00:04:28.477
Oh my gosh,
I just got another one!

00:04:28.518 --> 00:04:30.896
Wow, guess you've
totally mastered this game.

00:04:30.937 --> 00:04:32.147
There's no competing with you!

00:04:32.189 --> 00:04:34.524
Yeah, you've got this!

00:04:34.566 --> 00:04:35.442
[KEIICHI]
Amazing.

00:04:35.484 --> 00:04:36.943
That's no competition.

00:04:36.985 --> 00:04:40.197
She turned her game into
the Rika Furude Fan Club!

00:04:40.238 --> 00:04:41.656
Whenever you're ready, Maebara.

00:04:41.698 --> 00:04:43.450
[KEIICHI]
Uh! Sorry, guys.

00:04:45.786 --> 00:04:47.412
Here we go.

00:04:47.913 --> 00:04:51.541
Now I gotta pay a 50,000
dollar fine for tax evasion?

00:04:51.583 --> 00:04:52.959
Something wrong, Keiichi?

00:04:53.001 --> 00:04:54.961
Are you having a bad time?

00:04:55.003 --> 00:04:55.712
Are you?

00:04:55.754 --> 00:04:58.048
Everyone but you
won their games already.

00:04:58.089 --> 00:04:59.257
[KEIICHI]
Dangit!

00:04:59.299 --> 00:05:00.383
Mii.

00:05:00.425 --> 00:05:02.636
How much money
do you guys have right now?

00:05:02.677 --> 00:05:06.723
I have, uh, 980,000
thousand dollars.

00:05:06.765 --> 00:05:11.353
Uh, 880,000, and there's
still enough time to catch up!

00:05:11.394 --> 00:05:14.064
Huh? They're both on track
to have well over a million

00:05:14.105 --> 00:05:15.232
by the end of the game!

00:05:15.273 --> 00:05:17.734
So, how's that account
balance lookin', Kei?

00:05:17.776 --> 00:05:18.860
[KEIICHI]
Hey, shut up.

00:05:18.902 --> 00:05:22.072
This game is pure luck
and I keep getting bad spins!

00:05:22.113 --> 00:05:23.573
Save the excuses.

00:05:23.615 --> 00:05:25.784
No giving up allowed, Keiichi!

00:05:26.827 --> 00:05:30.580
Keiichi. Don't worry about it.

00:05:30.622 --> 00:05:31.498
[sighs]

00:05:31.540 --> 00:05:32.958
All I'm doing
is spinning the wheel!

00:05:32.999 --> 00:05:34.835
You think I'm missing
something, Mion?

00:05:34.876 --> 00:05:35.919
Then tell me!

00:05:35.961 --> 00:05:37.587
Come on, really?

00:05:37.629 --> 00:05:38.713
We were all playing to win,

00:05:38.755 --> 00:05:41.216
but you've been
putting in no effort at all.

00:05:41.258 --> 00:05:43.134
Wh‐What does that even mean!

00:05:43.176 --> 00:05:45.262
It wouldn't take ten seconds
to seal this game,

00:05:45.303 --> 00:05:47.472
but I guess you don't wanna win.

00:05:47.514 --> 00:05:48.515
Let's go.

00:05:48.557 --> 00:05:51.810
Don't you think that
was a little harsh, Mion?

00:05:52.853 --> 00:05:53.645
Damn it.

00:05:53.687 --> 00:05:55.772
Don't act like I'm not trying!

00:05:55.814 --> 00:05:57.023
It's a game of chance!

00:05:57.065 --> 00:05:58.817
How do you figure
I could guarantee a win,

00:05:58.859 --> 00:06:01.027
let alone get it done
in ten seconds?

00:06:01.069 --> 00:06:04.239
Am I destroying your hopes
and dreams with my crappy luck?

00:06:04.281 --> 00:06:07.200
So, uh, are we
gonna keep playing?

00:06:08.326 --> 00:06:11.746
You can always forfeit if
you don't feel like finishing.

00:06:13.290 --> 00:06:14.374
Play to win, huh?

00:06:14.416 --> 00:06:16.293
Fine then, let's go!

00:06:18.169 --> 00:06:19.087
Here's a thought.

00:06:19.129 --> 00:06:21.298
What say we make a deal, boys?

00:06:21.339 --> 00:06:22.507
You let me win.

00:06:22.549 --> 00:06:24.092
‐‐What?
‐‐What?

00:06:24.134 --> 00:06:27.304
Hey, hold on Maebara, using
threats is against the rules!

00:06:27.345 --> 00:06:28.680
Just settle down for a sec.

00:06:28.722 --> 00:06:30.599
Think about what
you're playing for here.

00:06:30.640 --> 00:06:31.600
The cash, right?

00:06:31.641 --> 00:06:33.435
Well, yeah, obviously!

00:06:33.476 --> 00:06:35.270
Let's say you win
this whole thing.

00:06:35.312 --> 00:06:37.480
What do you plan on
doing with the money?

00:06:37.522 --> 00:06:39.441
What do you think
you'd spend it on?

00:06:39.482 --> 00:06:40.984
I'd prob'ly buy a new game.

00:06:41.026 --> 00:06:43.111
Snacks or soda I guess.

00:06:43.153 --> 00:06:44.654
[chuckles]

00:06:44.696 --> 00:06:45.614
Come on, fellas.

00:06:45.655 --> 00:06:47.240
Ya gotta think big!

00:06:48.241 --> 00:06:50.493
Okay? So what are
you gonna do with it

00:06:50.535 --> 00:06:53.246
that's so much better than
what we would do with it?

00:06:53.288 --> 00:06:54.539
I'm glad you asked.

00:06:54.581 --> 00:06:56.583
Us club members are
playing for the prize too,

00:06:56.625 --> 00:06:59.419
but we also face a penalty
for any game we lose!

00:06:59.461 --> 00:07:00.587
And the winner is allowed

00:07:00.629 --> 00:07:03.089
to determine the loser's
penalty without exception.

00:07:03.131 --> 00:07:04.507
You're the only
club member here,

00:07:04.549 --> 00:07:06.343
your punishment
is your problem.

00:07:06.384 --> 00:07:07.302
What does that have to do with‐‐

00:07:07.344 --> 00:07:08.595
Hear me out.

00:07:08.637 --> 00:07:11.890
Tomita, you have a huge crush
on Satoko, don't you?

00:07:12.349 --> 00:07:15.518
And you, Okamura,
you have the hots for Rika.

00:07:16.144 --> 00:07:19.522
Hah. Think what I can
do for you if I win.

00:07:19.564 --> 00:07:22.734
Tomita, how do you feel about
Satoko wearing a collar,

00:07:22.776 --> 00:07:26.196
playing your
little sister for a day?

00:07:28.198 --> 00:07:29.324
[KEIICHI]
And Okamura.

00:07:29.366 --> 00:07:31.201
Would you care
to take a leisurely stroll

00:07:31.242 --> 00:07:33.286
with your new cat, Rika?

00:07:33.328 --> 00:07:35.121
I can make it happen.

00:07:39.167 --> 00:07:40.335
‐‐I could never ask for that.
‐‐Hold on, there's no way.

00:07:40.377 --> 00:07:41.962
‐‐But I mean...
‐‐Sounds nice, but...

00:07:42.003 --> 00:07:43.922
Easy now.
You're not in the club,

00:07:43.964 --> 00:07:47.384
and it's not your fault if the
penalty I choose benefits you.

00:07:47.425 --> 00:07:50.136
It's too late now for me to
escape a lonely teenhood.

00:07:50.178 --> 00:07:51.638
but at least there's still hope

00:07:51.680 --> 00:07:53.682
for the kids coming
up behind me!

00:07:53.723 --> 00:07:54.474
Help me out here,

00:07:54.516 --> 00:07:57.227
and I can offer you a prize
far greater than money!

00:07:57.268 --> 00:07:59.688
I swear it on my manly pride!

00:08:00.814 --> 00:08:03.274
‐‐Thank you, Maebara!
‐‐Thank you, Maebara!

00:08:03.316 --> 00:08:05.527
[TOMITA] I'll follow
you to hell and back!

00:08:06.695 --> 00:08:08.697
[ALL 3]
That's the game!

00:08:08.738 --> 00:08:10.115
So it's over?

00:08:10.156 --> 00:08:11.741
Who won, Keiichi?

00:08:11.783 --> 00:08:13.785
In the end, I claimed victory.

00:08:13.827 --> 00:08:14.661
[shocked sounds]

00:08:14.703 --> 00:08:17.622
How did you pull it off after
that dismal beginning you had?

00:08:17.664 --> 00:08:19.791
It's all about knowing
your opponents.

00:08:19.833 --> 00:08:21.001
Isn't that right?

00:08:21.042 --> 00:08:22.544
‐‐Yeah!
‐‐Yeah!

00:08:24.379 --> 00:08:26.798
So Keiichi does
have what it takes!

00:08:26.840 --> 00:08:29.300
Heh! That was just
the preliminaries.

00:08:29.342 --> 00:08:31.720
No way I'm gonna be
the one to get knocked out!

00:08:31.761 --> 00:08:34.556
Hmph. Guess you can
play to win after all.

00:08:34.597 --> 00:08:36.099
Good for you, Kei!

00:08:36.141 --> 00:08:36.933
All right.

00:08:36.975 --> 00:08:39.728
So what game are we gonna
play for the final round?

00:08:39.769 --> 00:08:40.562
What game?

00:08:40.603 --> 00:08:41.980
Yes, about that.

00:08:43.940 --> 00:08:47.444
See the thing is, my shift
is actually about to start.

00:08:47.485 --> 00:08:49.112
‐‐[TOMITA] Why?
‐‐[OKAMURA] No!

00:08:52.490 --> 00:08:53.616
[MION]
Sorry, everyone.

00:08:53.658 --> 00:08:56.077
I'll make it up to you
next time, promise!

00:08:56.119 --> 00:08:58.496
You kids made the shop
a lot of money today!

00:08:58.538 --> 00:09:00.790
Here, take these
as a "thank you."

00:09:01.916 --> 00:09:02.959
Hold on a minute.

00:09:02.959 --> 00:09:04.252
I helped out too.

00:09:04.294 --> 00:09:05.336
Where's mine?

00:09:05.378 --> 00:09:07.839
I'll give you a big tip the
next time I see you at work.

00:09:07.881 --> 00:09:09.632
[sighs]
Really?

00:09:09.674 --> 00:09:11.009
Well hello there!

00:09:11.051 --> 00:09:12.552
I got a new penguin friend!

00:09:12.594 --> 00:09:15.638
Oh my gosh can
I actually take this home?

00:09:15.680 --> 00:09:18.141
So is mine cute too?

00:09:18.183 --> 00:09:19.893
[RENA gasps]

00:09:19.934 --> 00:09:21.686
It's so kyute!

00:09:21.728 --> 00:09:22.854
[laughs]

00:09:22.896 --> 00:09:23.646
What's wrong, Kei?

00:09:23.688 --> 00:09:26.524
Don't you wanna take it home
and play house with it?

00:09:26.566 --> 00:09:28.109
It is pretty cute, honestly.

00:09:28.151 --> 00:09:30.320
Just not exactly what I'm into.

00:09:30.361 --> 00:09:32.822
And if you keep it, folks in
town are gonna start talking

00:09:32.864 --> 00:09:34.908
about the weird kid
with the doll.

00:09:34.949 --> 00:09:35.950
Good point.

00:09:35.992 --> 00:09:39.204
This would be wasted on me.

00:09:39.245 --> 00:09:41.206
Hmm...

00:09:41.247 --> 00:09:44.042
Keiichi.

00:09:44.084 --> 00:09:46.044
That could be a
good gift for someone.

00:09:46.086 --> 00:09:48.171
And if you give it out of the
goodness of your heart,

00:09:48.213 --> 00:09:51.633
I know anybody here would
be happy to accept it!

00:09:53.885 --> 00:09:55.386
You should have this, Mion.

00:09:55.428 --> 00:09:57.472
I think it suits
you much better.

00:09:57.514 --> 00:09:58.181
You what?

00:09:58.223 --> 00:10:01.226
Oh, no, I'm not really into
all that girly‐girl stuff!

00:10:01.267 --> 00:10:03.394
Sometimes it's like I was
supposed to end up a guy,

00:10:03.436 --> 00:10:05.980
but the wrong box got
checked or something!

00:10:06.022 --> 00:10:08.691
Seriously, just take it!

00:10:08.733 --> 00:10:11.236
Jeez. Thank you.

00:10:11.277 --> 00:10:12.529
I think that's for the best.

00:10:12.570 --> 00:10:16.199
Keiichi may have won her,
but she's better off with you.

00:10:33.216 --> 00:10:34.801
I'd say this food
isn't much different

00:10:34.843 --> 00:10:36.886
from any other
family restaurant.

00:10:36.928 --> 00:10:39.389
Nobody comes here
for the food, Keiichi.

00:10:39.430 --> 00:10:41.057
Just take a look.

00:10:45.520 --> 00:10:48.857
Excuse me! Could I get
another coffee here please?

00:10:48.898 --> 00:10:51.234
'Kay. Be right there!

00:10:51.442 --> 00:10:55.488
[ICHIRO hmms appreciatively]

00:10:55.530 --> 00:10:58.616
Seriously? That's the
reason people come here?

00:10:58.658 --> 00:11:00.326
[ICHIRO]
Be honest.

00:11:00.368 --> 00:11:02.954
You do understand
the appeal, don't you?

00:11:02.996 --> 00:11:05.415
Ow! That was
totally uncalled for.

00:11:05.456 --> 00:11:07.500
